# RBAC Rules

## Purpose
Enforce role and permission model in `docs/RBAC.md` at API and UI layers.

## Requirements
- Permission codes: `{module}.{resource}.{action}` seeded in DB.
- Roles: super_admin, org_owner, org_admin, sales_manager, sales_executive, telecaller, marketing_user, client.
- `@RequirePermissions()` decorator matches API_SPEC authorization column.
- Data scope filters in services (assigned-only for sales_executive).
- Field-level: use serialization groups / response mappers per role.
- Update RBAC.md when adding permissions.

## Restrictions
- No role checks via hardcoded email lists.
- Client role cannot call internal `/employees` routes.
- Telecaller cannot `properties.delete` or `employees.delete`.

## Best Practices
- `/auth/me` returns `permissions: string[]` for frontend gating.
- Integration test matrix: role × endpoint × expected status.
- Super Admin impersonation requires audit log entry.

## Anti-Patterns
- Single `isAdmin` boolean for all authorization.
- Checking role name strings in 20 places — use permission codes.

## Examples

```typescript
@RequirePermissions('inquiries.assign')
@Patch(':id/assign')
assign(@Param('id') id: string, @Body() dto: AssignDto) { ... }
```
